---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<DocsLayout frontmatter={{ title: "Documentation", description: "Craftplan user guides and documentation" }}>
  <p>
    Welcome to the Craftplan documentation. These guides cover every major
    feature of the platform, from initial setup to day-to-day operations.
  </p>

  <h2>Getting Started</h2>
  <p>
    New to Craftplan? Start with the <a href={`${base}docs/getting-started/`}>setup guide</a> to
    get a local instance running, then read the <a href={`${base}docs/overview/`}>Overview &amp; Planner</a> guide
    to learn how the main workspace is organized.
  </p>

  <h2>Feature Guides</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/overview/`}>Overview &amp; Planner</a> &mdash; The landing page with schedule, make sheet, and materials tabs</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/catalog/`}>Catalog &amp; BOMs</a> &mdash; Products, BOM editor, versioning, labor steps, and pricing</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/inventory/`}>Inventory</a> &mdash; Materials, lots, stock movements, allergens, and forecasting</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/orders/`}>Orders</a> &mdash; Order lifecycle, statuses, calendar view, and invoicing</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/purchasing/`}>Purchasing</a> &mdash; Suppliers, purchase orders, and receiving</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/production-batching/`}>Production Batching</a> &mdash; Batch workflow from allocation to completion</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/customers/`}>Customers</a> &mdash; Customer database, addresses, and order history</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/settings/`}>Settings</a> &mdash; General configuration, markup, allergens, CSV import/export</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>API</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${base}docs/api/`}>API Reference</a> &mdash; Interactive JSON:API documentation with endpoint details, schemas, and examples</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
